# 📖 Project Context References

## Key Files to Understand Project Structure

When working on this project, familiarize yourself with:

### Configuration Files

- `config/django/test.py` - Test-specific settings
- `config/django/test_fast.py` - Fast test settings (if exists)
- `pyproject.toml` or `setup.py` - Project dependencies

### Core Structure

- `models/` - Database models
- `controllers/` - Request handlers (views)
- `services/` - Business logic layer
- `selectors/` - Retrival logic layer
- `serializers/` - Data validation and serialization
- `serializers/` - Data validation and serialization
- `permissions/` - Shared permissions
- `handlers/` - Signals of the project
- `tests/` - Test suite mirroring source structure

## When Starting New Features

1. Review similar existing implementations
2. Check models for available methods
3. Look at existing tests for patterns
4. Follow established patterns

